      "writtenOn": "2020-05-29T06:26:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note that users can already set canary percentage to 0 for some builders, so even waiting infinitely long doesn\u0027t prevent latent bugs from showing up when switching canary-\u003eprod.\n\nMy thought was that users shouldn\u0027t be setting NO here for many builders unless they are swearing off canary coverage. Maybe I can add this to the documentation here:\n\n\"\"\"\n  Note that setting these to \"NO\" for large swaths of your builders will cause us to miss your builders when proposing new production changes. We (ChOps Foundation) rely on canary signals to ensure that proposed production changes are safe. If you opt out many of your builders, it means we won\u0027t have coverage for them, and when we flip from canary to prod, any missed bugs will cause ALL of your builders to immediately break.\n \n  It\u0027s still reasonable, however, to opt out some builders which you need to be \"extra stable\", but are otherwise functionally represented elsewhere in canary. For example, if you have some \u0027official\u0027 builders which are practically mirrored by non-official builders, it could be reasonable to opt the official builders out.\n\"\"\"",
      "parentUuid": "711f7e26_9520e5b0",
      "revId": "c60d300046f10b58a1d066d4947b5fd0eb7a3810",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
