      "writtenOn": "2020-05-29T16:27:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "+1 to allow user-controlled opt in/out, which will be ignored after a certain communicated deadline.\n\nwrt surfacing leftover options, I used LUCI Config-propagated warnings, but these are only happening when config is modified. I was thinking we should have automated bug filing or at least email on a weekly basis + dashboard for whom to nag. Surfacing via builds would be useful for small projects where all devs are actually doing some infra work.",
      "parentUuid": "ae3be5ab_85d06ece",
