      "writtenOn": "2020-05-29T18:23:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "my main concern is leftover cruft. I think we should generally try to keep things clean. \n\nIf we continue adding things without cleaning them up, at some point it will turn into a mess. For this reason, when it comes to temporary things I generally prefer to keep them in a tightly-controlled places, like settings.cfg or even code. Public APIs are not tightly controlled.\n\nI think there is a contradiction above:\n- one hand it says \"if they were proactive enough to set it in the first place\", implying there will be *few* users.\n- on the other hand, it says \"we have to hand-hold all users\" implying *a lot* of users.\n\nI think there will be few users because it is an advanced feature.\nI don\u0027t see what\u0027s the problem for power users to modify settings.cfg in such an exception case. This is not a mainstream feature. Users already modify other files in the same repo (bots.cfg).\n\n\u003e deal with reverts and conflicts, etc.\n\nThis seems far-fetched to me.\n\nfurther, actually using this feature via cr-bulidbucket.cfg also means we will need to extend starlark to generate it. This is more work and more temporary cruft. Are we going to cleanup starlark too?\n\nGiven the track record of not following through with cleanups in the past, when it comes to temporary stuff, my personal preference is for approaches where cleanups are easier, to increase the likelyhood of them actually happening in a timely manner.\n\nSo I am not opposed to this change if cleanup actually happens right after bbagent is rolled out everywhere. But also there is a caveat: this approach seems to be more work (because of starlark) so I am not clear why would we chose this path.",
      "parentUuid": "73c5ac7c_919eb385",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 466,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 466,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "c60d300046f10b58a1d066d4947b5fd0eb7a3810",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
